s questions of performance. The girlish story that lurks in the background but actually forms the framework of the poem now becomes more clear, revealing at the same time the didactic objective of the poet. A new edition of the Partheneion and the Scholia is offered at the end, together with a new translation of the poem.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aAlkman. 4aGriechische Poesie. 4aMädchenlieder / Griechische Poesie. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aAlcman.  aGreek Archaic Poetry.  aMaiden Chorus.  aPartheneion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062109908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE CLASSICAL STUDIES 2012z9783110293838oZDB-23-DGD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2012z9783110288964oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311029182740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311029200840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110292008423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110292008/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062109-9  DGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPD